# Laravel API Customers Demo

Simple CRUD REST API demo using MSON.

## Customers Collection [/customers]

### List All Customer [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (array[Customer])

### Create a New Customer [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "name": "Kilian",
            "surname": "Rubiella",
            "email": "kilian@demo.es"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Customer)
    
+ Response 422 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[ValidationError])
            

## Customers Management [/customers/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id: 120 (number) - Customer unique identifier
    

### Show Customer [GET]

+ Request (application/json)
    
+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (Customer)


### Update Customer [PUT]

+ Request (application/json)

+ Response 200 (application/json)
     + Attributes (Customer)

+ Response 422 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[ValidationError])


### Delete Customer [DELETE]

+ Request (application/json)

+ Response 204 (application/json)


